In Florida, Medicaid eligibility for adults is very limited. Florida has not expanded Medicaid under the ACA. For a head of household with one child (household size of 2), the income threshold for parents/caretaker relatives is approximately 26% of the Federal Poverty Level, and for other pathways the limits are similarly very low.

With $190,020 in total income, this household's income far exceeds any Medicaid income threshold in Florida, even considering the disability status of the adult. The household is not eligible for Medicaid.
